3E%3Cp%3EThe%20demands%20of%20infancy%20felt%20brand%20new%2C%20yet%20I%20didn't%20have%20the%20luxury%20of%20slowly%20adjusting.%20Bills%20didn't%20wait%2C%20and%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-save-money-as-a-big-family-young-kids-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efamily%20of%20six%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20simply%20existing%20came%20with%20a%20steep%20price%20tag.%20I%20needed%20to%20work%2C%20and%20not%20just%20casually%20%E2%80%94%20I%20needed%20to%20hustle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225294c8d9-3e57-4aef-b463-a7bc42484b21%5C%22%3EMy%20husband%20and%20I%20work%20hard%2C%20but%20I%20realized%20it%20was%20coming%20at%20a%20cost%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20threw%20myself%20into%20multiple%20freelance%20jobs%20that%20allowed%20me%20to%20work%20remotely%2C%20stacking%20contracts%20and%20chasing%20every%20opportunity%20to%20ensure%20my%20family%20had%20what%20they%20needed.%20But%20what%20started%20as%20a%20necessity%20quickly%20became%20an%20all-consuming%20force.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20and%20I%20now%20work%20over%20110%20hours%20a%20week%20combined.%20While%20we're%20grateful%20to%20have%20steady%20work%2C%20it%20has%20definitely%20come%20at%20a%20cost.%20My%20youngest%20daughter%20has%20started%20vocalizing%20what%20I've%20been%20afraid%20to%20acknowledge%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20see%20you%20anymore.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20words%20hit%20me%20like%20a%20brick%20because%20she%20was%20right.%20I%20had%20spent%20months%20tunnel-visioned%20on%20survival%2C%20trying%20to%20keep%20up%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmy-husband-helped-save-thousands-family-grocery-bill-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epay%20for%20groceries%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20medical%20bills%2C%20school%20supplies%2C%20and%20everything%20in%20between.%20In%20doing%20so%2C%20I%20was%20missing%20the%20very%20moments%20that%20made%20it%20all%20worthwhile.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMotherhood%20is%20a%20consta